Job Description: 
A vacancy for an IT/IM Security Manager has arisen within Airbus Defence and Space (ADS) in Ottobrunn/Taufkirchen with working location in Hallbergmoos. 
The successful applicant will join TZISM Subsidiary Management and M&A 

Information Management (IM) delivers the expertise, technology and equipment for Airbus Space and Aerospace products – We make it fly! 
IM is transforming and evolving but, we need even more talented people who can make a real difference to how we support, enable and deliver a diverse range of technological solutions and services to our internal and external customers and partners . 
What does this mean for you? A role in IM is an opportunity for you to grow and to develop your career in a progressive and innovative environment. 
Our people the teams they work in and the values embedded in IM, are driving this change and you could be part of that too. 

Within the DTO Organisation Services, Solution, M&A our team is responsible for the non Core sites of ADS, with a strong focus on Customer Service Sites / the International Sites of ADS and also for providing IT/IM services for our customers / Partners. One of these customers is the Eurofighter GmbH located in Hallbergmoos for which ADS is providing the IT services for Infrastructure, Enduser- and Application Support 

Are you passionate for digital security and interested in further improving the digital world of our customer ? Then join us as an IIT/IM Security Manager. 

In collaboration with the Service Delivery and IT Operations Managers you are responsible for 

provide secure operation of the Services; 
reacts to security notifications, alerts, information security incidents and warnings (especially notifications from BSI and CERTs) and evaluates the relevance for the Services; 
being point of contact for all questions of information security; 
monitors the patch status of the systems in use and takes measures to remedy any security Incidents; 
conducts regular audits of the infrastructure and appication landscape and eliminates vulnerabilities; 
is part of the team for compliance with Customer’s and contractual information security requirements; 
participates in business impact analyses; 
conducts security risk assessments; 
designs and implements control mechanisms and plans for information security; 
documents and updates procedures for the operation of control mechanisms related to information security; 
monitors security breaches and management of security Incidents; 
reports to the Customer and analyses KPIs of information security and the initiation of measures; 
carries out information security tests; 
ensures compliance with the security-relevant Service Levels. 
PoC for the central Security Operation Center 


You should have at least 5 years of work experience in a similar position and be open to work in a multinational team. 
Please be aware that this position requires a respective Security clearance (Ü2) 

A Bachelor / Master degree in Information technology with an emphasis in Cyber Security would be beneficial but can be easily compensated by an according work experience. 

This job requires an awareness of any potential compliance risks and a commitment to act with integrity, as the foundation for the Company’s success, reputation and sustainable growth. 

Company: Airbus Defence and Space GmbH 

Contract Type: Permanent Contract / CDI / Unbefristet / Contrato indefinido 

Experience Level: Professional / Expérimenté(e) / Professionell / Profesional 

Job Family: Cyber Security <JF-CG-ST> 

By submitting your CV or application you are consenting to Airbus using and storing information about you for monitoring purposes relating to your application or future employment. This information will only be used by Airbus.  Airbus is committed to achieving workforce diversity and creating an inclusive working environment. We welcome all applications irrespective of social and cultural background, age, gender, disability, sexual orientation or religious belief. 
Airbus is, and always has been, committed to equal opportunities for all. As such, we will never ask for any type of monetary exchange in the frame of a recruitment process. Any impersonation of Airbus to do so should be reported to emsom@airbus.com . 

At Airbus, we support you to work, connect and collaborate more easily and flexibly. Wherever possible, we foster flexible working arrangements to stimulate innovative thinking.
